Auth model verified:
  - JWT for matching workspace → 200 (loadApproval + workspace match).
  - JWT for different workspace → 403 (wrong_workspace).
  - Malformed/missing JWT, no token → 401.
  - Signed token whose sha256 matches access_token_hash → 200 (unit tested).
  - Signed token mismatch → 401.

NOTIFY contract verified end-to-end:
  - Channel: `approval_<uuid_underscored>` — matches worker's channelFor() in
    worker/src/approvals/await.ts:78-81 EXACTLY (both replace /-/g with '_').
  - Worker's sql.listen handler re-queries `SELECT status FROM approvals
    WHERE id=<id>` after NOTIFY, resolves the awaitApproval promise. This
    contract held under both single-POST and bulk decide.

Side-effect ordering verified:
  - UPDATE approvals (status, decided_by, decided_at) lands first.
  - INSERT cloud_activity (approval_granted | approval_denied) lands next.
  - pg_notify on the per-id channel fires last.
  - All three commit before the response returns (each db.execute is its
    own auto-commit txn against the tx-mode pooler; NOTIFY is delivered
    to LISTENers on the session-mode pooler at :5432 because Supabase
    routes NOTIFY at the database-server layer, below the pooler).
